.SH "NAME"
lightning-listchannels \- Command for returning data on active lightning channels\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBlistchannels\fR [\fIshort_channel_id\fR]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fBlistchannels\fR RPC command returns data on channels that are known to the node\&.
.sp
If no \fIshort_channel_id\fR is supplied, then data on all lightning channels that are known to this node, are returned\&.
.sp
Supplying \fIshort_channel_id\fR will filter the results to only return data on a channel with a matching \fIshort_channel_id\fR, if one exists\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.sp
On success, an object with a "channels" key is returned containing a list of 0 or more objects\&.
.sp
